                <h4>What is the voting age population of Petersburg, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Petersburg, West Virginia, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 2,227.  The voting age population is 49.7% male and 50.3% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Petersburg, West Virginia residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 27.7% of
                        the residents of Petersburg are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Petersburg, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Petersburg are 95.1% White, 1.9% Black, 1.5% Other and 1.5% Two or more races. Additionally, 2.1% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Petersburg, West Virginia residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Petersburg, 10.9% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 11.8%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    5.0% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Petersburg.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Petersburg, West Virginia residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 52.9% of
                    Petersburg residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Petersburg, West Virginia residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    82.0% of
                    Petersburg residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 22.3%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 8.3%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Petersburg, West Virginia residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Petersburg residents aged 5 and older, 3.7% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                2.9% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                0.6% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.0% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Petersburg, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Petersburg is 10.9%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Petersburg, West Virginia residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Petersburg, 18.9% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
